<br>
      I think sony might have tripped up, I think getting some new stuff to do with GOD for the ele guilds was a good idea, but when you pound down an expansion down everyones throat every time you log on, with order it buttons or Later buttons on a splash screen, so you are doom to see it over and over again, (this wasn't just shown to the ele guild people to anoy, obviously) they should have some goodies for at least some of the casual gamers to make it worth it.<br>
    I am glad GOD helped to get some air into the upper end of the game, I heard it was getting kind of same old same old, and people needed a challenge. I know it made them feel, Finally someone did something for us..and good for them.<br>
<br>
But...<br>
<br>
    Its sometimes quite a long time between expansions, (in gaming terms, 8 months is a long time) if the expansion was going to be so hard core, they shouldn't have pounded it in so hard to everyone accross the board.<br>
<br>
Would it have killed them to expand a bit on a few more instant dungeons for not so hard core folks,  I think thats what everyone is kind of disapointed in, many people like the instant dungeons allot, and well some of us felt left out in the cold when they were foolish enough to fork up the cash in hopes of some more instant fun...<br>
<br>
but alas... I guess we will have to wait another year and hope for the bottle to point our way again... seems silly to me...But I don't want to begrudge someone elses fun, I just wish I was included, Being included in a year or two when I'm ready takes all the fun right out of it, by then it will be old hat.<br>
<br>
I think they built up some hopes, we got excited and held our breathe for the release. And splat, reality hit us, and some people were let down being left out..after being flogged with promo's<br>
<br>
