<br>
To give you an idea, on my server my 'Twink farm crew' that I was part of (check my wizard twink), regulary killed:<br>
* Statue / Avatar of War / Tormax<br>
* Farmed BoT Towers<br>
* Farmed Vex Thal<br>
* Killed off Seru, Emperor, Cursed <br>
* Killed off Progression Flag Mobs (Every flag mob in PoP)<br>
* Killed off elemental plane minis (hydrotha, krizlik, offossa, fire minis, etc).<br>
<br>
This is one, of three 'farming crews' that was started in the last 3-8 months - AFTER finishing the content. Did we compete with guilds that needed the content? No, we competed with other farming crews, or other guilds that had progressed far beyond the content. <br>
<br>
Tormax kill with 2 people / 6 characters, avatar of war kills with 4 people 13 characters? Elemental minis with 9 people / 21 characters? BoT towers with 2 people? Yep. All of that is content that is better served being killed off guilds / people that can actually use it on their mains. The only problem is they had no chance in hell in actually finding the content up so they could kill it. <br>
<br>
What GoD does is help out old content so it becomes more accessible, the game more enjoyable for those doing that content - while at the same time for the first time in 18 months giving the 'ubers' a place to progress to and play and have fun in.<br>
<br>
Also, I think you are wrong when you say you think most people are below 65. I think the large majority of players got at least one lvl 65 character - it's just that easy to get these days. <p><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=182398">Aebriol the Minstrel</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
